    <p class="article__paragraph">One of the most important reasons to protect animals is their role in maintaining healthy ecosystems. Predators, prey, and plant-eaters all play unique parts in keeping nature balanced. When species disappear due to habitat loss, hunting, or exploitation, entire ecosystems can suffer. The loss of even one species can trigger a domino effect that harms other wildlife, plant life, and ultimately, human populations that depend on those ecosystems for resources and stability.</p>
